1
00:00:01,134 --> 00:00:02,669
Mon!

2
00:00:04,904 --> 00:00:06,673
Oh, my God!

3
00:00:13,586 --> 00:00:14,828
Sorry.

4
00:00:14,828 --> 00:00:17,379
- Hi, Arci, welcome. - Hello.
[Filipina Actress Arci Muñoz]

5
00:00:17,379 --> 00:00:19,719
- Hello.
- Sorry, sorry.

6
00:00:19,719 --> 00:00:21,721
Jodi!

7
00:00:21,721 --> 00:00:23,656
We're so loud when we speak Filipino.

8
00:00:23,656 --> 00:00:26,659
- Long time! Oh, my God.
- Oh, my God.

9
00:00:26,659 --> 00:00:28,461
- Hello!
- Take a seat!

10
00:00:28,461 --> 00:00:30,096
Stay here for now.

11
00:00:30,096 --> 00:00:32,632
- Arci, we're still practicing.
- It's okay.

12
00:00:32,632 --> 00:00:33,933
Please sit here for now.

13
00:00:33,933 --> 00:00:36,545
- Stay here for now, sorry.
- Okay.

14
00:00:37,571 --> 00:00:38,912
Yes.

15
00:00:39,672 --> 00:00:41,474
Kumusta!

16
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:45,112
"Kumusta" is...

17
00:00:45,112 --> 00:00:47,047
"How have you been?"

18
00:00:47,047 --> 00:00:48,581
In Korean.

19
00:00:50,350 --> 00:00:51,584
[Kumusta]

20
00:00:51,584 --> 00:00:56,957
[The Big Table]

21
00:00:56,957 --> 00:00:59,592
- Jodi.
- How are you?

22
00:00:59,592 --> 00:01:01,327
When did you guys get here?

23
00:01:01,327 --> 00:01:04,064
The other, other, other day.

24
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:06,132
We've been here a week.
Well, I've been here a week.

25
00:01:06,132 --> 00:01:08,168
- You've been here for a week?
- One week.

26
00:01:08,168 --> 00:01:09,569
But I'll be staying.

27
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:11,771
I will stay for one more week.

28
00:01:11,771 --> 00:01:14,607
But I always come back and forth.

29
00:01:14,607 --> 00:01:17,911
- Korea is like a second home.
- Oh, my gosh.

30
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:20,447
There's so much to see.

31
00:01:20,447 --> 00:01:23,249
So I come here almost every month.

32
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:24,351
I'm so jealous.

33
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:26,720
You're so fluent in Korean.

34
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:29,556
I'm not fluent. Oh my gosh, no.

35
00:01:29,556 --> 00:01:33,059
I'm like, how do we even
run a restaurant with...

36
00:01:33,059 --> 00:01:34,594
I mean, so how do you do it?

37
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:37,697
Well, we're just, I guess,
blessed to have customers

38
00:01:37,697 --> 00:01:41,586
who kind of understand
broken Korean, or if not...

39
00:01:41,586 --> 00:01:42,769
Charades!

40
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:45,105
You just have to describe.

41
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:47,874
Oh, earlier, I couldn't explain the pork.

42
00:01:47,874 --> 00:01:49,122
So I just said: "Oink oink."

43
00:01:49,122 --> 00:01:50,743
Oh, my gosh!

44
00:01:50,743 --> 00:01:52,946
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, my God!

45
00:01:55,260 --> 00:01:56,716
What do you want to drink?

46
00:01:56,716 --> 00:01:57,851
I ordered beer.

47
00:01:57,851 --> 00:02:01,955
Beer! Oh, right.
Sorry, we got distracted by the chit-chat.

48
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:03,690
Beer

49
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:04,791
for you.

50
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,460
Oh, thank you. Appreciate it.

51
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,496
- Thank you, Jodi!
- Okay.

52
00:02:09,496 --> 00:02:12,436
Order 9 is for Arci.

53
00:02:12,436 --> 00:02:14,501
- That one?
- Yes.

54
00:02:14,501 --> 00:02:17,371
Sinigang, inasal, palabok, halo-halo.

55
00:02:17,371 --> 00:02:19,931
Get ready on the order of Arci.

56
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:21,448
Let's just serve them everything,

57
00:02:21,448 --> 00:02:23,356
so that her diet fails.

58
00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:34,254
I'm starving.

59
00:02:34,254 --> 00:02:36,389
Oh, my gosh.

60
00:02:36,389 --> 00:02:40,093
You didn't give Chef
the order for table number...

61
00:02:40,093 --> 00:02:41,428
- One?
- What?

62
00:02:43,379 --> 00:02:45,832
- Yeah. It's still here.
- Did I not give it?

63
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:48,001
Oh, my gosh, I'm so sorry!

64
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:50,337
Chef, sorry, my bad.

65
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:53,040
I didn't give you the order for Table 1.

66
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:55,552
Table 1 is...

67
00:02:55,552 --> 00:02:56,621
I'm so sorry.

68
00:02:56,621 --> 00:02:59,229
That was when Arci arrived.

69
00:02:59,229 --> 00:03:00,379
Okay.

70
00:03:00,379 --> 00:03:01,481
I'm so sorry!

71
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:02,815
- No worries.
- We'll just kind of...

72
00:03:02,815 --> 00:03:04,984
entertain them, I'll give them whatever.

73
00:03:04,984 --> 00:03:07,086
Yeah, we'll give them a free something.

74
00:03:07,086 --> 00:03:09,395
We'll jump. Let's prioritize this.

75
00:03:09,889 --> 00:03:12,059
- I'm sorry.
- Oh, it's okay.

76
00:03:12,059 --> 00:03:13,694
Okay.

77
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:16,462
I am sorry for the delay.

78
00:03:16,462 --> 00:03:18,765
Because of that, I'll give you...

79
00:03:22,041 --> 00:03:23,442
A special treat.

80
00:03:24,130 --> 00:03:25,906
- Sorry.
- Oh, thank you.

81
00:03:25,906 --> 00:03:28,621
For... For waiting. Sorry.

82
00:03:28,621 --> 00:03:30,189
Thank you.

83
00:03:31,778 --> 00:03:33,513
This is for you.

84
00:03:35,114 --> 00:03:37,241
Oh, this looks better, right?

85
00:03:37,241 --> 00:03:38,851
So, in total, we have two sini...

86
00:03:38,851 --> 00:03:40,276
- Okay, let's do one at a time.
- Yeah, two Sinigang.

87
00:03:40,276 --> 00:03:41,639
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

88
00:03:45,826 --> 00:03:46,927
Okay.

89
00:03:47,994 --> 00:03:49,963
This doesn't have enough water.

90
00:03:56,769 --> 00:03:57,904
Okay.

91
00:04:04,044 --> 00:04:05,112
Okay.

92
00:04:05,812 --> 00:04:08,348
Sinigang for Table 1.

93
00:04:08,348 --> 00:04:09,413
And then...

94
00:04:10,284 --> 00:04:11,651
That's it.

95
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,177
Palabok...

96
00:04:14,177 --> 00:04:16,177
Table 1.

97
00:04:17,223 --> 00:04:20,360
Hello, sorry for the wait.
This is your sinigang.

98
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:23,229
Let me get your bowls for you.

99
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:29,702
This smells familiar.

100
00:04:29,702 --> 00:04:31,371
Oh, it looks delicious.

101
00:04:32,038 --> 00:04:33,139
Here.

102
00:04:34,007 --> 00:04:35,809
Smells like ginseng chicken soup.

103
00:04:35,809 --> 00:04:38,979
Yes, it's actually like a pork back-bone stew,
but this one is more...

104
00:04:38,979 --> 00:04:40,894
- Ah, pork back-bone stew?
- Sour?

105
00:04:41,483 --> 00:04:43,335
It's more... it's more sour.

106
00:04:43,335 --> 00:04:44,350
Filipino style!

107
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:45,918
- Sour?
- Yes.

108
00:04:45,918 --> 00:04:47,172
It's Filipino style.

109
00:04:47,172 --> 00:04:48,187
Wow.

110
00:04:48,187 --> 00:04:49,491
- Oh, thank you!
- Here.

111
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:51,624
Enjoy!

112
00:04:51,624 --> 00:04:53,559
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

113
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:57,128
I've never had food
with this type of sour taste before.

114
00:05:04,071 --> 00:05:05,465
This is good!

115
00:05:06,069 --> 00:05:07,540
- Oh, it's sour.
- Yeah.

116
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:08,956
My style, my style.

117
00:05:09,842 --> 00:05:11,778
Here's your palabok.

118
00:05:11,778 --> 00:05:13,513
Please enjoy!

119
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:15,548
- Wow!
- Thank you!

120
00:05:15,548 --> 00:05:16,716
Wow!

121
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:24,223
This looks so good.

122
00:05:24,223 --> 00:05:25,592
This kind of reminds me of curry.

123
00:05:25,592 --> 00:05:27,927
- It's kinda like glass noodles.
- The portions are huge.

124
00:05:34,968 --> 00:05:36,103
How is it?

125
00:05:39,605 --> 00:05:40,807
That is so good.

126
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:42,640
No, seriously, that's so good.

127
00:05:46,276 --> 00:05:47,306
I'm giving them...

128
00:05:47,306 --> 00:05:49,552
I'm giving Table 1 an extra portion.

129
00:05:49,552 --> 00:05:50,654
Because we...

130
00:05:50,654 --> 00:05:51,931
- Of inasal?
- Yeah.

131
00:05:51,931 --> 00:05:54,487
I'll just say it's a little gift for them.

132
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:57,857
Yes. And then say, "We apologize for..."

133
00:05:57,857 --> 00:05:59,103
The waiting.

134
00:05:59,103 --> 00:06:00,136
Okay.

135
00:06:00,136 --> 00:06:02,929
Hi, this is your garlic rice.

136
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:07,293
And you ordered one chicken inasal,
but we made it two.

137
00:06:07,293 --> 00:06:09,436
Just as a "sorry" for the waiting.

138
00:06:09,436 --> 00:06:11,589
- Okay, thank you.
- Yes.

139
00:06:11,589 --> 00:06:13,319
Please enjoy!

140
00:06:19,448 --> 00:06:20,868
Wow!

141
00:06:21,981 --> 00:06:24,317
I wanted to try these together.

142
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,103
Good? Good?

143
00:06:30,857 --> 00:06:32,276
No good!

144
00:06:32,276 --> 00:06:33,711
Very good!

145
00:06:35,461 --> 00:06:39,532
I'm just so happy
because nobody is making complaints.

146
00:06:39,532 --> 00:06:41,434
If ever we do receive complaints,

147
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:45,805
Then we'll just have to say: "Sorry, sorry..."

148
00:06:45,805 --> 00:06:49,862
There's nothing we can do. Just say sorry.

149
00:06:49,862 --> 00:06:51,978
If someone says, "We don't like it",

150
00:06:51,978 --> 00:06:54,280
I'll be like, "Alright, I'll have it then."

151
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:56,949
You'll be paying for them anyway.

152
00:06:58,618 --> 00:06:59,862
This is...

153
00:06:59,862 --> 00:07:01,521
Her sinigang.

154
00:07:01,521 --> 00:07:03,589
Then we'll serve the palabok and inasal?

155
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:04,924
- Yeah.
- Okay.

156
00:07:05,658 --> 00:07:06,793
Okay.

157
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:09,103
Sinigang, please for Ms. Arci.

158
00:07:09,103 --> 00:07:10,937
Okay!

159
00:07:12,699 --> 00:07:13,967
Alright.

160
00:07:14,535 --> 00:07:15,861
Okay.

161
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:20,306
Good evening!

162
00:07:20,306 --> 00:07:21,441
Hi!

163
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,414
We're serving you your palabok.

164
00:07:23,414 --> 00:07:25,411
- Oh, my God.
- And your plain rice.

165
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:27,513
- Hi, good evening.
- Hi!

166
00:07:27,513 --> 00:07:29,081
- Hi, Chef.
- Hello, how are you?

167
00:07:29,081 --> 00:07:32,852
I think we've met each other
in an event in Dubai.

168
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:34,687
During "Global Filipino".

169
00:07:34,687 --> 00:07:36,923
Oh, my gosh, it's a long time ago.

170
00:07:36,923 --> 00:07:38,491
With Martin?

171
00:07:38,491 --> 00:07:40,059
Yeah, I think so.

172
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:42,395
Please sit down, enjoy your meal.

173
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:45,345
- Inasal, palabok, and then...
- Thank you, Chef.

174
00:07:45,345 --> 00:07:46,932
- Okay, sure.
- Go ahead.

175
00:07:46,932 --> 00:07:48,034
Let's eat!

176
00:07:48,034 --> 00:07:49,722
- You guys eat first.
- Enjoy.

177
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,373
Is it delicious?

178
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:05,241
Oh, this is good.

179
00:08:05,241 --> 00:08:06,766
Delicious.

180
00:08:11,091 --> 00:08:13,894
You know what the best sinigang
I've ever tasted is?

181
00:08:14,727 --> 00:08:16,362
In New York.

182
00:08:16,362 --> 00:08:17,797
- Wow.
- "Wow", really?

183
00:08:17,797 --> 00:08:19,332
Wow, it was so delicious.

184
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,267
Let's change that, Arci.

185
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:22,897
Let's make that
the best sinigang you've ever had.

186
00:08:22,897 --> 00:08:24,437
Correct. Yes.

187
00:08:24,437 --> 00:08:25,838
It's in Korea!

188
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:27,073
Yes!

189
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:31,577
What are the odds?

190
00:08:31,577 --> 00:08:34,514
Your best sinigang is not in the Philippines,

191
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:37,183
but in New York, and now, here in Korea.

192
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,151
She cooked it and...

193
00:08:39,151 --> 00:08:40,920
She made it.

194
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:42,321
You're the one who cooked?

195
00:08:42,321 --> 00:08:43,856
- Some of it. The sinigang, yes.
- The sinigang.

196
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:45,357
Wow!

197
00:08:45,357 --> 00:08:47,794
What did you say?
You tried the one from New York?

198
00:08:47,794 --> 00:08:52,932
No, she said, like, she tasted
the best sinigang in New York.

199
00:08:52,932 --> 00:08:56,102
And now, it's going to be Korea.

200
00:08:56,102 --> 00:08:57,203
What?

201
00:08:59,171 --> 00:09:00,473
Which...

202
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:04,114
There's this restaurant in New York
that I always go to. Oh, my God.

203
00:09:04,114 --> 00:09:06,102
- Tradisyon?
- Tradisyon!

204
00:09:06,102 --> 00:09:08,281
- That's my friend.
- Oh, my gosh, their sinigang.

205
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:10,983
Yeah, but now here, it's in Korea.

206
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:13,719
- Go tell him...
- What?

207
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:16,379
Say: "Anton! Someone beat your sinigang."

208
00:09:16,379 --> 00:09:17,657
Yes.

209
00:09:17,657 --> 00:09:20,500
Next time, they won't serve you
any sinigang in New York.

210
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:26,333
Thank you, Chef, for the food.

211
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:28,294
- Say hi to Anton.
- I will!

212
00:09:29,001 --> 00:09:31,835
Oh, my gosh, see? Small world.

213
00:09:32,638 --> 00:09:33,839
Hello!

214
00:09:34,656 --> 00:09:35,841
Good evening.

215
00:09:35,841 --> 00:09:38,740
So, would you like to check your bill?

216
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:41,448
- Thank you, take care.
- Goodbye.

217
00:09:41,448 --> 00:09:43,316
Sleep well. Good night.

218
00:09:43,316 --> 00:09:44,250
Bye-bye.

219
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,086
- Thank you, Jodi.
- Thank you, sir.

220
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:47,387
Bye-bye.

221
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:56,629
How are you doing, sweetie?

222
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:57,997
- This is...
- Are you tired?

223
00:09:57,997 --> 00:09:59,034
The life of an OFW.

224
00:09:59,034 --> 00:10:00,600
Life's really like this here in Korea.

225
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,035
It's tough, but we manage.

226
00:10:03,035 --> 00:10:04,437
You can do it! Fighting!

227
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:05,780
Fighting!

228
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,141
Wow, just wow.

229
00:10:09,141 --> 00:10:10,843
There's a lot to clean up.

230
00:10:13,069 --> 00:10:15,181
I'm getting overwhelmed over here.

231
00:10:15,181 --> 00:10:17,034
We'll be able to clean this.

232
00:10:17,034 --> 00:10:18,552
We're many.

233
00:10:26,207 --> 00:10:27,609
Hello!

234
00:10:28,194 --> 00:10:29,562
Can we get the bill?

235
00:10:30,162 --> 00:10:31,330
Oh, my God!

236
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:33,295
I'm sorry, auntie.

237
00:10:33,295 --> 00:10:34,433
Just call me sis.

238
00:10:34,433 --> 00:10:35,724
"Auntie" might be a little too much.

239
00:10:35,724 --> 00:10:36,802
Okay.

240
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:37,904
Jodi!

241
00:10:37,904 --> 00:10:39,599
Cashier.

242
00:10:41,574 --> 00:10:43,897
- Aw, thank you.
- Thank you.

243
00:10:43,897 --> 00:10:46,586
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

244
00:10:46,586 --> 00:10:50,116
- Thank you for coming.
- Good food, good service.

245
00:10:50,116 --> 00:10:51,784
- Thank you.
- Jodi.

246
00:10:51,784 --> 00:10:53,285
Thank you.

247
00:10:55,637 --> 00:10:56,756
Take care.

248
00:10:56,756 --> 00:10:58,691
Thank you. Thank you so much.

249
00:10:58,691 --> 00:11:00,026
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

250
00:11:00,026 --> 00:11:01,494
I stink.

251
00:11:03,483 --> 00:11:04,530
Thank you!

252
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:05,655
- Bye-bye. Good night.
- Thank you.

253
00:11:05,655 --> 00:11:07,357
Take care.

254
00:11:12,738 --> 00:11:14,483
We can flip the sign now, right?

255
00:11:14,483 --> 00:11:16,040
I think so.

256
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:21,915
[Closed]

257
00:11:21,915 --> 00:11:23,183
Wow.

258
00:11:24,483 --> 00:11:25,617
Okay.

259
00:11:27,087 --> 00:11:28,526
Let's start.

260
00:11:36,996 --> 00:11:39,298
Excuse me.

261
00:11:41,878 --> 00:11:42,902
Yuck.

262
00:11:42,902 --> 00:11:46,964
Now I know why they tell you
to finish your food.

263
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,642
- Sorry, Lord.
- That's a lot of waste, huh?

264
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:50,943
- A lot.
- Oh, sorry.

265
00:11:50,943 --> 00:11:53,517
- That's a lot.
- Sorry, Lord.

266
00:11:53,517 --> 00:11:55,127
Let's do this first.

267
00:11:59,085 --> 00:12:00,119
I'll just put them here.

268
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:01,620
Okay, go.

269
00:12:03,022 --> 00:12:04,870
There's still so much left.

270
00:12:11,690 --> 00:12:13,085
Heavy!

271
00:12:15,435 --> 00:12:17,293
Heavy!

272
00:12:19,606 --> 00:12:20,813
Voilá.

273
00:12:21,875 --> 00:12:23,109
Those are being cleaned now.

274
00:12:23,109 --> 00:12:25,946
Maybe you can put them in the right...

275
00:12:29,849 --> 00:12:31,917
I miss my dog.

276
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:33,586
I miss...

277
00:12:36,288 --> 00:12:38,324
I miss everybody.

278
00:12:39,158 --> 00:12:40,926
Sorry, Chef. I'll handle it.

279
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:42,328
I'll just do this first.

280
00:12:42,328 --> 00:12:45,231
Almost done, almost done.

281
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:48,802
I want to check the time.

282
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:53,739
I need air, I need air!

283
00:12:55,841 --> 00:12:57,484
Wait, my legs...

284
00:12:58,177 --> 00:13:01,280
I wonder what's going to happen to us tomorrow.

285
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,249
I don't think I could be a dishwasher.

286
00:13:03,249 --> 00:13:04,448
- You think you can't?
- I don't think I can.

287
00:13:04,448 --> 00:13:05,518
The whole day?

288
00:13:05,518 --> 00:13:06,719
Respect to the dishwasher.

289
00:13:06,719 --> 00:13:08,487
- Yes!
- Geez.

290
00:13:09,655 --> 00:13:13,058
And then when you call the waiter,

291
00:13:13,058 --> 00:13:15,906
you'll call them with so much respect now,

292
00:13:15,906 --> 00:13:18,372
because you know how hard it is.

293
00:13:18,372 --> 00:13:19,598
Insane.

294
00:13:24,009 --> 00:13:27,301
[All Clear]

295
00:13:27,301 --> 00:13:28,925
Yeah!

296
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:30,910
Ah!

297
00:13:32,411 --> 00:13:34,280
Good Lord.

298
00:13:50,297 --> 00:13:52,432
My foot is hurting.

299
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:01,140
Is it bad to have that feeling when you...

300
00:14:01,140 --> 00:14:04,009
When you have one last customer,

301
00:14:04,009 --> 00:14:07,713
you're thinking:
"Can you just leave already..."

302
00:14:07,713 --> 00:14:09,148
It's normal.

303
00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:11,524
I will never be the last customer

304
00:14:11,524 --> 00:14:13,652
- in any restaurant.
- Don't. Don't.

305
00:14:13,652 --> 00:14:15,487
Never eat on the last call.

306
00:14:15,487 --> 00:14:20,826
I'm so sorry to all the restaurants
I've been a pain at.

307
00:14:20,826 --> 00:14:23,195
I don't even have energy to celebrate.

308
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,801
Me, too.

309
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:30,903
But her... Wow. She got burned, but...

310
00:14:31,503 --> 00:14:33,572
I thought...

311
00:14:33,572 --> 00:14:35,486
She was unfazed.

312
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,945
Gotta do what you gotta do.

313
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,749
As for her, I saw the...

314
00:14:43,749 --> 00:14:46,574
She's smiling, but you can see

315
00:14:46,574 --> 00:14:48,092
- she's not really happy.
- Me?

316
00:14:48,092 --> 00:14:49,121
- Her.
- No, me.

317
00:14:49,121 --> 00:14:50,189
Ah, I thought...

318
00:14:50,189 --> 00:14:52,192
It's slowly coming out...

319
00:14:52,192 --> 00:14:53,626
- Exhaustion.
- Your eyes!

320
00:14:53,626 --> 00:14:55,327
It's really obvious when you're tired.

321
00:14:55,327 --> 00:14:56,362
- Yeah.
- Super.

322
00:14:56,362 --> 00:14:58,397
I remember even when we...

323
00:14:58,397 --> 00:15:00,132
On the set of "Be Careful with My Heart."

324
00:15:00,132 --> 00:15:01,634
When we were working.

325
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:04,390
- The eyes. They don't lie.
- Never lie.

326
00:15:05,966 --> 00:15:07,968
Ah, what a day.

327
00:15:10,009 --> 00:15:11,977
I can't wait for my cheeseburger.

328
00:15:14,246 --> 00:15:16,483
Tomorrow's another day and I think...

329
00:15:16,483 --> 00:15:17,483
We need help!

330
00:15:17,483 --> 00:15:18,851
- Yeah, because remember...
- Were we like that before?

331
00:15:18,851 --> 00:15:20,786
It's so hard to wash the dishes and like,

332
00:15:20,786 --> 00:15:22,000
cook at the same time.

333
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,760
And you guys are serving.

334
00:15:25,241 --> 00:15:27,793
Maybe we should hire someone.

335
00:15:27,793 --> 00:15:29,995
We can't do it, just the four of us.

336
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:32,759
Two people running the front of the house,

337
00:15:32,759 --> 00:15:34,366
two people running the kitchen?

338
00:15:34,366 --> 00:15:35,894
Oh, Lord.

339
00:15:39,372 --> 00:15:41,040
Oh my God!

340
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:45,138
Okay, what if, I mean I don't know.

341
00:15:45,138 --> 00:15:49,966
Would you give in and ask for help?

342
00:15:49,966 --> 00:15:52,414
Maybe we need one more.

343
00:15:52,414 --> 00:15:54,165
But the thing is, who could it be?

344
00:16:02,138 --> 00:16:04,063
- Okay.
- Okay.

345
00:16:04,063 --> 00:16:06,533
Alright, let's clean up and go home.

346
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:08,020
Yeah.

347
00:16:08,635 --> 00:16:10,120
Ouch.

348
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:18,340
[Close 10:30 PM]

349
00:16:24,069 --> 00:16:25,684
[Yeongdong Traditional Market]
This is the market.

350
00:16:25,684 --> 00:16:27,886
I'm excited for this.

351
00:16:29,121 --> 00:16:32,691
Oh, my God. Wow, their market!

352
00:16:32,691 --> 00:16:35,394
It's extremely clean and calm.

353
00:16:37,779 --> 00:16:41,033
- Look at their rice cakes!
- I know!

354
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:42,436
So...

355
00:16:43,102 --> 00:16:46,005
What we have to buy is sea bream?

356
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:47,973
- Yes.
- Sea bream.

357
00:16:48,607 --> 00:16:49,641
Pork knuckles.

358
00:16:49,641 --> 00:16:51,076
Wow!

359
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:52,911
Pork knuckles are a thing here?

360
00:16:54,754 --> 00:16:55,914
Is that famous here?

361
00:16:55,914 --> 00:16:57,750
I don't know, but it's nice.

362
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,619
It smells sweet.

363
00:16:59,619 --> 00:17:00,920
But we're here for fish.

364
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:03,223
Okay. Eyes on the prize.

365
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:05,824
- Okay.
- Okay.

366
00:17:05,824 --> 00:17:08,494
Are we not allowed to buy food?

367
00:17:09,795 --> 00:17:12,414
Let's buy later,
but we have to get the fish first.

368
00:17:12,414 --> 00:17:13,552
Okay.

369
00:17:13,552 --> 00:17:16,268
We have a new dish today, right?

370
00:17:16,268 --> 00:17:18,537
- And it's a sea bream.
- Yeah.

371
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:20,506
- Salt-crusted.
- Yes.

372
00:17:20,506 --> 00:17:23,108
And they're going to love it.

373
00:17:24,326 --> 00:17:25,377
Okay.

374
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:27,312
But right now, we're like...

375
00:17:27,312 --> 00:17:29,748
I mean, we're like a kid in the candy store.

376
00:17:29,748 --> 00:17:31,884
I'm getting distracted.

377
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:33,485
- Look at this.
- Oh, kimchi.

378
00:17:33,485 --> 00:17:34,552
Wait.

379
00:17:34,552 --> 00:17:37,222
Okay, I also want to take a picture of this.

380
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:39,425
Oh, wow. There are different kinds of kimchi.

381
00:17:39,425 --> 00:17:40,759
I know!

382
00:17:40,759 --> 00:17:42,061
Look at their rice cakes!

383
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:44,496
Wait, that looks so good.

384
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:46,365
Oh, that's so cute.

385
00:17:46,365 --> 00:17:47,733
Wait a second.

386
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,301
This got my attention.

387
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:51,336
Cute.

388
00:17:51,336 --> 00:17:52,838
Oh, it says Philippines. Look.

389
00:17:52,838 --> 00:17:53,939
What?

390
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:55,660
The thingy!

391
00:17:58,207 --> 00:17:59,771
Pilipinas!

392
00:18:04,517 --> 00:18:05,584
- There it is!
- There.

393
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:09,276
I thought I smelled something fishy,
and here it is.

394
00:18:09,276 --> 00:18:10,722
Look at this.

395
00:18:10,722 --> 00:18:12,024
It's so fresh.

396
00:18:12,959 --> 00:18:14,207
Hi.

397
00:18:14,207 --> 00:18:15,208
Hello.

398
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:19,131
- Hi! Hello!
- Hello.

399
00:18:19,131 --> 00:18:20,379
How are you?

400
00:18:21,291 --> 00:18:22,367
What are we looking for?

401
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:24,336
Sea bream.

402
00:18:24,336 --> 00:18:26,505
- Domi?
- Domi?

403
00:18:26,505 --> 00:18:28,340
Ah, this one.

404
00:18:32,241 --> 00:18:33,931
There, it's not slimy.

405
00:18:34,966 --> 00:18:35,998
Then...

406
00:18:36,931 --> 00:18:37,966
There!

407
00:18:39,234 --> 00:18:40,352
What's that?

408
00:18:40,352 --> 00:18:42,488
You can see how fresh it is.

409
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:44,983
- Ah, okay.
- Then you smell it.

410
00:18:47,426 --> 00:18:48,862
You can smell that?

411
00:18:48,862 --> 00:18:49,995
I can't.

412
00:18:49,995 --> 00:18:51,373
Gimme your...

413
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:57,870
It's not... It smells like the sea.

414
00:18:57,870 --> 00:18:58,971
Ah, okay.

415
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:04,143
And the eyes, they're crystal clear.

416
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,644
That means they're still fresh?

417
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:07,479
Yes, it's not cloudy.

418
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:08,547
Okay.

419
00:19:08,547 --> 00:19:10,415
Should we get...

420
00:19:10,415 --> 00:19:12,284
Can you ask him how much?

421
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:16,788
- How much is it?
- 15,000 won.

422
00:19:18,624 --> 00:19:21,126
1,500...

423
00:19:21,126 --> 00:19:23,362
Ah, okay, and then the discount.

424
00:19:24,229 --> 00:19:26,064
Discount, please?

425
00:19:26,064 --> 00:19:27,966
No, this is already cheap.

426
00:19:27,966 --> 00:19:29,586
Discount, please?

427
00:19:29,586 --> 00:19:30,636
We charge only the cost price.

428
00:19:30,636 --> 00:19:31,904
- Okay.
- He doesn't want to.

429
00:19:31,904 --> 00:19:34,506
Okay, okay. No problem.

430
00:19:37,621 --> 00:19:38,677
How many?

431
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:42,014
Let's get a few. Let's get maybe...

432
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,815
Fifteen pieces?

433
00:19:43,815 --> 00:19:45,384
- Fifteen pieces?
- Yeah.

434
00:19:45,384 --> 00:19:47,186
So, that's around one box?

435
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:48,820
I think so.

436
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:50,088
Can I get one box, please?

437
00:19:50,088 --> 00:19:51,523
Okay, here you go.

438
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:53,655
- Mission accomplished.
- Yes.

439
00:19:53,655 --> 00:19:55,133
Picture!

440
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:02,534
He's so cute.

441
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:04,636
Okay, thank you!

442
00:20:15,382 --> 00:20:17,021
Another day?

443
00:20:19,069 --> 00:20:22,287
I think we're the last ones to get here.

444
00:20:22,287 --> 00:20:23,856
The late ones.

445
00:20:24,423 --> 00:20:26,572
I hope everything is okay.

446
00:20:26,572 --> 00:20:27,646
Alright.

447
00:20:28,448 --> 00:20:30,379
Hi! Good morning!

448
00:20:30,379 --> 00:20:31,897
- Good morning!
- Hey guys!

449
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:33,599
Right on cue!

450
00:20:34,166 --> 00:20:37,302
- Hello!
- She's here!

451
00:20:37,302 --> 00:20:38,870
Good morning!

452
00:20:38,870 --> 00:20:42,161
I'm Ramona, nice to meet you.

453
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:44,943
Welcome to Korea!

454
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:47,379
We need help.

455
00:20:47,379 --> 00:20:49,448
Maybe we should hire someone.

456
00:20:49,448 --> 00:20:51,350
Okay, she told me earlier:

457
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,985
"I'll be here for a week."

458
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,421
You think she would?

459
00:20:57,055 --> 00:20:58,123
Hello?

460
00:20:58,123 --> 00:20:59,691
<i>Jodi, is that you?</i>

461
00:20:59,691 --> 00:21:01,493
- Yes, it's me.
<i>- Is this you?</i>

462
00:21:01,493 --> 00:21:02,961
Yes, it's me!

463
00:21:02,961 --> 00:21:05,697
<i>Yes, Jodi!</i>

464
00:21:05,697 --> 00:21:07,666
Did you like the food earlier?

465
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:10,871
<i>Yes. It was good. Delicious.</i>

466
00:21:10,871 --> 00:21:13,040
Are you going to be busy tomorrow?

467
00:21:14,308 --> 00:21:16,453
<i>Tomorrow...</i>

468
00:21:17,576 --> 00:21:20,178
<i>I was just planning to wander around,
but nothing much.</i>

469
00:21:20,178 --> 00:21:21,348
<i>I'm not busy.</i>

470
00:21:21,348 --> 00:21:25,751
If your plans
aren't super important tomorrow...

471
00:21:25,751 --> 00:21:29,855
Then maybe you can chill out
here in our resto...

472
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:31,556
If it's okay, if it's okay!

473
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,960
<i>I guess it's okay.</i>

474
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:37,129
<i>I can drop everything tomorrow.</i>

475
00:21:37,828 --> 00:21:38,897
We love you.

476
00:21:38,897 --> 00:21:40,800
<i>Jodi, you've got to remember that I'm here.</i>

477
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,101
<i>I'm like...</i>

478
00:21:42,101 --> 00:21:44,189
<i>I am Korean. Just kidding.</i>

479
00:21:44,189 --> 00:21:45,704
What was that?

480
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,909
<i>I'm basically Korean, I'm Korean.</i>

481
00:21:51,276 --> 00:21:55,276
We'll serve the fish
and the chicken together with the rice.

482
00:21:55,276 --> 00:22:00,966
One sinigang, one gising-gising,
one halo-halo, please!

483
00:22:02,552 --> 00:22:04,656
It's really slippery.

484
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:06,103
- One more fish.
- Yeah.

485
00:22:06,103 --> 00:22:07,426
One more palabok.

486
00:22:07,426 --> 00:22:08,552
And gising-gising.

487
00:22:08,552 --> 00:22:10,662
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

488
00:22:10,662 --> 00:22:13,131
Come this way, is that okay?

489
00:22:13,131 --> 00:22:14,633
Garlic rice.

490
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:16,134
Enjoy your meal.

491
00:22:16,803 --> 00:22:20,839
[Arci Muñoz All Rounder]

492
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:22,227
Nice!

493
00:22:22,841 --> 00:22:24,743
- Give me a hug!
- What's up, ketchup?

494
00:22:25,579 --> 00:22:27,212
What's up, ketchup?

495
00:22:42,448 --> 00:22:43,966
[17 minutes to go]
Seventeen minutes.

496
00:22:43,966 --> 00:22:45,964
Okay. Ready?

497
00:22:45,964 --> 00:22:47,999
Okay, I'm good with the appetizer.

498
00:22:47,999 --> 00:22:51,185
Alright. Garlic, onions...

499
00:22:51,185 --> 00:22:52,271
and lemongrass.

500
00:22:52,271 --> 00:22:54,239
Just three things.

501
00:22:54,239 --> 00:22:56,207
This partner of mine...

502
00:22:56,207 --> 00:22:58,310
She's only been in the kitchen for two days.

503
00:22:58,310 --> 00:22:59,753
But it's like...

504
00:23:00,427 --> 00:23:02,181
Like she's been here for a week.

505
00:23:02,181 --> 00:23:04,750
Imagine after one week,
it's going to feel like a month in.

506
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:06,719
Sorry, I'm just pressuring you.

507
00:23:06,719 --> 00:23:08,587
I'm just trying to toughen you up.

508
00:23:08,587 --> 00:23:09,654
You might jinx it.

509
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:12,691
Kitchens do have some pressure.

510
00:23:12,691 --> 00:23:15,627
For me, when I cook,
I don't want anyone in the kitchen.

511
00:23:15,627 --> 00:23:17,345
I want just me.

512
00:23:17,345 --> 00:23:18,764
Yeah.

513
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:22,167
I don't like people watching me
when I'm cooking.

514
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:25,303
Okay, we open!

515
00:23:25,303 --> 00:23:26,638
I'll open it up now.

516
00:23:26,638 --> 00:23:28,173
- Yes, sweetheart.
- Okay.

517
00:23:29,341 --> 00:23:32,277
[Day 2]
[12:00 PM]

518
00:23:42,107 --> 00:23:43,276
[Today's Menu: Sea Bream]

519
00:23:43,276 --> 00:23:45,223
This is salt-crusted sea bream.

520
00:23:45,223 --> 00:23:48,059
Our signature dish for today.

521
00:23:48,059 --> 00:23:49,795
We're open!

522
00:23:49,795 --> 00:23:52,715
- Restaurant's open!
- Okay.

523
00:23:53,965 --> 00:23:56,101
This is it. My dreams are really coming true.

524
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:58,403
To become a chef. Joke.

525
00:24:06,711 --> 00:24:08,247
Hi!

526
00:24:08,247 --> 00:24:10,081
Hi.

527
00:24:10,081 --> 00:24:11,650
- Hello!
- Hello!

528
00:24:11,650 --> 00:24:12,951
- Hello, countrymen!
- Hello.

529
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:14,553
Filipino!

530
00:24:14,553 --> 00:24:15,720
Oh, Philippines!

531
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,222
- Hello! How are you?
- Philippines!

532
00:24:17,222 --> 00:24:19,724
- Thank you for coming!
- Yes, hello.

533
00:24:19,724 --> 00:24:21,827
I've heard there's something interesting here.

534
00:24:21,827 --> 00:24:22,961
And that's why I came.

535
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:25,232
- Yes, yes, yes, yes.
- And I want to give it a try.

536
00:24:25,232 --> 00:24:26,733
- Have a seat for a moment.
- Sit down for a bit.

537
00:24:26,733 --> 00:24:30,268
Is it okay if I take some videos?

538
00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:31,770
- No problem.
- For my vlog!

539
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:32,966
Go ahead.

540
00:24:32,966 --> 00:24:34,606
Are you okay to sit here?

541
00:24:34,606 --> 00:24:36,241
