00:37:46,564 --> 00:37:50,067
Wow, to be eating local food
right in the middle of Seoul.

813
00:37:53,671 --> 00:37:56,274
I feel like we'll have to wait again
until the next one.

814
00:38:05,449 --> 00:38:07,652
- Two inasal.
- Did they order garlic rice?

815
00:38:07,652 --> 00:38:09,453
- All done.
- Okay.

816
00:38:09,453 --> 00:38:10,821
Sorry for the delay.

817
00:38:11,379 --> 00:38:12,423
Alright, fish!

818
00:38:12,423 --> 00:38:13,491
Fish next.

819
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:16,794
This is done, this is done.

820
00:38:18,729 --> 00:38:20,100
Hello!

821
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:22,035
Chicken inasal.

822
00:38:23,901 --> 00:38:25,236
Enjoy!

823
00:38:26,370 --> 00:38:30,574
Hello. So, this is your chicken inasal.

824
00:38:31,175 --> 00:38:32,610
Place one over there...

825
00:38:33,724 --> 00:38:35,046
Chicken, two.

826
00:38:35,046 --> 00:38:37,081
Let me check. Excuse me.

827
00:38:37,081 --> 00:38:39,283
I guess it's one per order, right?

828
00:38:39,283 --> 00:38:42,787
I think this is the dish
that takes the longest.

829
00:38:49,207 --> 00:38:51,931
One more inasal for Table 5.

830
00:38:53,164 --> 00:38:54,198
This... right here.

831
00:38:54,198 --> 00:38:55,879
Ah! One more inasal!

832
00:38:55,879 --> 00:38:57,483
- Wait.
- Okay.

833
00:38:57,483 --> 00:38:59,655
Ah, what is that?

834
00:39:01,475 --> 00:39:05,409
I'm sorry, the inasal
will be coming out in a bit.

835
00:39:05,409 --> 00:39:07,611
Again, sorry for the delay.

836
00:39:07,611 --> 00:39:09,747
Thank you for your patience.

837
00:39:10,417 --> 00:39:15,322
[The wait continues]

838
00:39:16,557 --> 00:39:18,621
[New Table No.6]
Yes?

839
00:39:20,091 --> 00:39:21,379
One sinigang.

840
00:39:21,379 --> 00:39:22,514
And then...

841
00:39:22,514 --> 00:39:23,594
Palabok.

842
00:39:24,428 --> 00:39:26,297
Inasal.

843
00:39:26,297 --> 00:39:28,733
Okay, please wait a moment.

844
00:39:32,439 --> 00:39:34,572
Every time you come in, I'm scared.

845
00:39:34,572 --> 00:39:37,541
Okay, we got new order. We got sinigang.

846
00:39:37,541 --> 00:39:39,510
One palabok, one inasal.

847
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:41,615
Sinigang and palabok again.

848
00:39:41,615 --> 00:39:42,816
Yes!

849
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:47,385
[Inasal Grilling in Progress!]

850
00:39:53,958 --> 00:39:57,094
- That's to speed it up, right?
- Yes.

851
00:39:57,094 --> 00:39:58,929
So it gets coated better.

852
00:40:08,475 --> 00:40:11,342
Oh, I'm getting sleepy.

853
00:40:11,342 --> 00:40:13,077
Here's the appetizer.

854
00:40:14,779 --> 00:40:17,053
[Other Table Getting Served...]
So, this is your palabok.

855
00:40:18,717 --> 00:40:20,717
The sinigang.

856
00:40:22,553 --> 00:40:24,355
Inasal coming, coming.

857
00:40:25,379 --> 00:40:27,069
- I'll put some design into it.
- Yeah.

858
00:40:29,059 --> 00:40:30,161
Art.

859
00:40:30,161 --> 00:40:31,529
Atchara.

860
00:40:31,529 --> 00:40:33,064
There we go!

861
00:40:33,064 --> 00:40:34,635
Yum!

862
00:40:34,635 --> 00:40:35,766
I'm hungry.

863
00:40:35,766 --> 00:40:38,102
You're hungry? You poor thing...

864
00:40:38,102 --> 00:40:39,534
There you go!

865
00:40:40,340 --> 00:40:42,573
One inasal!

866
00:40:42,573 --> 00:40:44,414
- This is good to go?
- Yes!

867
00:40:44,414 --> 00:40:46,000
Table 6?

868
00:40:46,690 --> 00:40:48,148
Yes, Table 6.

869
00:40:50,981 --> 00:40:54,488
Hello, sorry for the wait,
this is your chicken inasal.

870
00:40:54,488 --> 00:40:55,985
Please enjoy.

871
00:40:56,957 --> 00:40:58,792
- Wow, it's really big.
- Exactly.

872
00:40:59,493 --> 00:41:02,663
I think they got the order wrong.

873
00:41:02,663 --> 00:41:05,525
They got served before us.

874
00:41:08,599 --> 00:41:11,268
Yeah, looks like our order went to their table.

875
00:41:16,507 --> 00:41:18,776
Okay, coming in.

876
00:41:18,776 --> 00:41:21,278
Then you make your design.

877
00:41:22,310 --> 00:41:24,281
I'll put lime.

878
00:41:24,281 --> 00:41:26,241
Yeah, there we go, okay.

879
00:41:26,241 --> 00:41:30,345
And then, coriander, onion... We can put chili.

880
00:41:31,822 --> 00:41:33,657
Let's put a tomato.

881
00:41:34,925 --> 00:41:37,578
Hold on, hold on. We got a little magic to do.

882
00:41:38,966 --> 00:41:40,241
Wow.

883
00:41:40,241 --> 00:41:41,475
Okay.

884
00:41:41,999 --> 00:41:45,178
[Salt-Crusted Sea Bream Completed]
- Service. - Service.

885
00:41:57,848 --> 00:41:59,183
Who ordered the fish?

886
00:41:59,183 --> 00:42:01,221
Please double-check, Chef, the table.

887
00:42:01,221 --> 00:42:04,155
They're Table 1, but... Wait, wait, wait, wait!

888
00:42:04,155 --> 00:42:06,490
- I'll ask, I'll ask.
- Yes, yes, yes.

889
00:42:06,490 --> 00:42:08,792
- Hi guys, did you order fish?
- Yeah.

890
00:42:08,792 --> 00:42:13,030
Okay, sorry for the wait.
It takes 20 minutes to cook.

891
00:42:17,935 --> 00:42:20,070
Didn't they also come after us?

892
00:42:21,438 --> 00:42:24,542
They got served with their fish dish.

893
00:42:25,676 --> 00:42:27,241
Maybe we're not getting ours...

894
00:42:27,241 --> 00:42:28,812
Was this it?

895
00:42:28,812 --> 00:42:30,883
I think there was a mix-up with the order.

896
00:42:33,690 --> 00:42:35,273
Excuse me?

897
00:42:35,897 --> 00:42:37,284
Excuse me?

898
00:42:37,284 --> 00:42:38,756
Yes?

899
00:42:38,756 --> 00:42:40,663
We finished the dish?

900
00:42:40,663 --> 00:42:41,759
The fish?

901
00:42:41,759 --> 00:42:44,628
Yeah, fish and one chicken.

902
00:42:44,628 --> 00:42:46,263
Okay. I'm so sorry for the wait.

903
00:42:46,263 --> 00:42:48,276
Let me get back.

904
00:42:48,276 --> 00:42:50,472
Are we still getting our food?

905
00:42:52,897 --> 00:42:54,338
Guys!

906
00:42:54,338 --> 00:42:58,742
The fish Chef served to Table 1
should've gone to Table 5.

907
00:42:58,742 --> 00:43:00,277
Where did Chef serve it?

908
00:43:00,277 --> 00:43:01,345
To Table 1.

909
00:43:02,586 --> 00:43:03,847
Why?

910
00:43:03,847 --> 00:43:07,885
Both Table 6 and Table 5 have inasal,
but Table 5 needs it more.

911
00:43:07,885 --> 00:43:09,987
They ordered first, yes...

912
00:43:09,987 --> 00:43:14,625
Earlier, I asked for the inasal at Table 6...

913
00:43:14,625 --> 00:43:16,270
[A moment ago]
There we go!

914
00:43:17,328 --> 00:43:19,130
- Is this good to go?
- Yes!

915
00:43:19,130 --> 00:43:20,497
Table 6?

916
00:43:20,497 --> 00:43:22,199
Yes, Table 6.

917
00:43:24,379 --> 00:43:26,690
Six, seven, six...

918
00:43:27,404 --> 00:43:29,852
Huh? It's already two?

919
00:43:29,852 --> 00:43:32,115
Chef? Oh, he's not here.

920
00:43:33,043 --> 00:43:35,420
Chef served the fish...

921
00:43:36,897 --> 00:43:38,332
Oh, my gosh.

922
00:43:43,862 --> 00:43:46,490
<i>Okay, now, my next agenda is</i>

923
00:43:46,490 --> 00:43:49,526
<i>to buy the thing I wanted to try.</i>

924
00:43:49,526 --> 00:43:50,661
<i>This one?</i>

925
00:43:50,661 --> 00:43:52,496
<i>Fermented bread!</i>

926
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:56,931
<i>Wow, look at this place!</i>

927
00:43:56,931 --> 00:43:58,302
<i>Wow, there's like a...</i>

928
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:00,104
<i>They make it at the back!</i>

929
00:44:00,104 --> 00:44:01,438
<i>Hello.</i>

930
00:44:01,438 --> 00:44:02,609
<i>Fermented bread?</i>

931
00:44:02,609 --> 00:44:04,842
<i>And one like this.</i>

932
00:44:04,842 --> 00:44:07,017
<i>Kinda want to try these also.</i>

933
00:44:07,017 --> 00:44:08,312
<i>One also.</i>

934
00:44:08,312 --> 00:44:11,081
<i>And this. I want to get this, too.</i>

935
00:44:11,081 --> 00:44:12,796
<i>I'm getting so many things.</i>

936
00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:14,852
<i>Thank you.</i>

937
00:44:18,322 --> 00:44:20,274
<i>What if I try it now?</i>

938
00:44:20,274 --> 00:44:21,392
<i>- Yeah.
- Let's try it.</i>

939
00:44:21,392 --> 00:44:22,926
<i>Okay.</i>

940
00:44:22,926 --> 00:44:24,069
<i>I'm curious.</i>

941
00:44:24,069 --> 00:44:25,073
<i>So...</i>

942
00:44:25,860 --> 00:44:27,011
<i>Okay, okay, okay...</i>

943
00:44:27,011 --> 00:44:28,732
<i>It looks sticky.</i>

944
00:44:28,732 --> 00:44:29,759
<i>Cheers!</i>

945
00:44:29,759 --> 00:44:30,793
<i>My hand is shaking.</i>

946
00:44:30,793 --> 00:44:33,230
<i>My hand is shaking.</i>

947
00:44:36,106 --> 00:44:38,107
<i>One fell.</i>

948
00:44:42,479 --> 00:44:43,940
<i>Not so sweet.</i>

949
00:44:45,149 --> 00:44:49,414
<i>It's like a crossbreed
between bread and rice cake.</i>

950
00:44:49,414 --> 00:44:50,862
<i>Rice cake.</i>

951
00:44:51,724 --> 00:44:52,966
<i>I like it.</i>

952
00:44:54,027 --> 00:44:56,033
<i>I like the stickiness of it.</i>

953
00:45:01,771 --> 00:45:05,552
<i>You really get to feel
the country in the market.</i>

954
00:45:05,552 --> 00:45:07,146
<i>Yeah.</i>
